From dtenenba at fredhutch.org  Mon Mar 21 16:58:31 2016
From: dtenenba at fredhutch.org (Dan Tenenbaum)
Date: Mon, 21 Mar 2016 08:58:31 -0700 (PDT)
Subject: [Bioc-devel] svn branching
In-Reply-To: <45491_1458569515_56F0012B_45491_4827_4_CAGwVkvYKWiKaLyCQeXTNbRMG8EGmeebwG6e9tUsmYmHonFi8Ng@mail.gmail.com>
References: <45491_1458569515_56F0012B_45491_4827_4_CAGwVkvYKWiKaLyCQeXTNbRMG8EGmeebwG6e9tUsmYmHonFi8Ng@mail.gmail.com>
Message-ID: <866365214.3554435.1458575911448.JavaMail.zimbra@fredhutch.org>

You can work in git (https://bioconductor.org/developers/how-to/git-mirrors/) and create as many local branches as you want.
You can't create any branches in svn. You have access only to your package, in devel (trunk) and the release branch.

If working in git, be wary of creating a non-linear commit history, this causes problems when trying to merge with svn.


Dan


